{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"IntersectionObserverEntry.intersectionRect","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/intersectionRect","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Intersection_Observer_API\">Intersection Observer API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry\"><code>IntersectionObserverEntry</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/boundingClientRect\"><code>boundingClientRect</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/intersectionRatio\"><code>intersectionRatio</code></a></li><li><em><code>intersectionRect</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/isIntersecting\"><code>isIntersecting</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/rootBounds\"><code>rootBounds</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/target\"><code>target</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/time\"><code>time</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Intersection Observer API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserver\"><code>IntersectionObserver</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/indexedDB\"><code>indexedDB</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry\"><code>IntersectionObserverEntry</code></a> interface's\n  read-only <strong><code>intersectionRect</code></strong> property is a\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRectReadOnly\"><code>DOMRectReadOnly</code></a> object which describes the smallest rectangle that\n  contains the entire portion of the target element which is currently visible within\n  the intersection root.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRectReadOnly\"><code>DOMRectReadOnly</code></a> which describes the part of the target element that's\n  currently visible within the root's intersection rectangle.\n</p>\n<p>\n  This rectangle is computed by taking the intersection of\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry\" title=\"boundingClientRect\"><code>boundingClientRect</code></a> with each of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/target\" title=\"target\"><code>target</code></a>'s ancestors' clip rectangles,\n  with the exception of the intersection <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserver/root\" title=\"root\"><code>root</code></a>\n  itself.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  In this simple example, an intersection callback stores the intersection rectangle for\n  later use by the code that draws the target elements' contents, so that only the visible\n  area is redrawn.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">intersectionCallback</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">entries</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  entries<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">forEach</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">entry</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    refreshZones<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">push</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">element</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>target<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token literal-property property\">rect</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>intersectionRect\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/IntersectionObserver/#dom-intersectionobserverentry-intersectionrect","title":"Intersection Observer"}],"query":"api.IntersectionObserverEntry.intersectionRect"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.IntersectionObserverEntry.intersectionRect","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/intersectionRect/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The IntersectionObserverEntry interface's\n  read-only intersectionRect property is a\n  DOMRectReadOnly object which describes the smallest rectangle that\n  contains the entire portion of the target element which is currently visible within\n  the intersection root.","popularity":0.0003,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:14:42.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/intersectionobserverentry/intersectionrect","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/intersectionobserverentry/intersectionrect/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/277e5969c63b97cfb55ab4a0e612e8040810f49b","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry","title":"IntersectionObserverEntry"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/intersectionRect","title":"IntersectionObserverEntry.intersectionRect"}],"pageTitle":"IntersectionObserverEntry.intersectionRect - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}